.TH "WINDOW.CLOSE" "3JS" "July 21, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Window.close \- Window: close() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Window.close()\f[B]\f[R] method closes the current
window, or the window on which it was called.
.PP
Windows are \f[I]script\-closable\f[R] if they were created by web
content.
This generally includes:
.IP \(bu 2
Windows opened using \f[CR]Window.open()\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
Windows opened via web content, such as links
(\f[CR]<a target=\(dq_blank\(dq>\f[R]) or forms
(\f[CR]<form target=\(dq_blank\(dq>\f[R]), without user modifier actions
.PP
Windows opened by browser UI actions \(em such as right\-click → Open in
new tab, Ctrl+Click, Shift+Click, or middle\-click \(em are often not
script\-closable.
They may only be closed if they have not been navigated (history length
remains 1).
Calling \f[CR]close()\f[R] otherwise typically shows a console warning:
\f[CR]Scripts may not close windows that were not opened by script.\f[R]
.PP
Note also that \f[CR]close()\f[R] has no effect when called on
\f[CR]Window\f[R] objects returned by
\f[CR]HTMLIFrameElement.contentWindow\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
close()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Closing a window opened with \f[CR]window.open()\f[R]
This example shows a method which opens a window and a second one which
closes the window; this demonstrates how to use
\f[CR]Window.close()\f[R] to close a window opened by calling
\f[CR]window.open()\f[R].
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// Global variable to store a reference to the opened window\f[R]
\f[B]let\f[R] openedWindow;

\f[B]function\f[R] openWindow() {
  openedWindow = window.open(\(dqmore\-info.htm\(dq);
}

\f[B]function\f[R] closeOpenedWindow() {
  openedWindow.close();
}
.EE
